Line spacing was incorrectly added to XAdvance (change didn't make any sense, value of XAdvance is not used anywhere).
Cropping rectangle width and height set to Subrect width and height, as XOffset and YOffset are essentially subrect X and Y:

In GlyphCropper:

``` C#
                glyph.Subrect.Y++;
                glyph.Subrect.Height--;

                glyph.YOffset++;
[...]
                glyph.Subrect.X++;
                glyph.Subrect.Width--;

                glyph.XOffset++;
```

Width of cropping rectangle is not used anywhere. Height of cropping rectangle is checked to see if its larger than the line spacing, but is never actually used.

In conclusion, this does not affect how the SpriteFont gets drawn on the screen.

I can't manage to handle the backbutton on this new WP8.1 template... On WP8.1, by default, the backbutton does not CLOSE the app, it just go to the background, and you can go back to it by long pressing the back button on the phone and selecting the app.
This is the guideline, just for reference:
http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/apps/xaml/dn639128.aspx

I've managed to stop this behaviour by doing this:

```
HardwareButtons.BackPressed += HardwareButtons_BackPressed;
private void HardwareButtons_BackPressed(object sender, BackPressedEventArgs e)
        {
            e.Handled = true;
        }
```

Inside InputEvents ctor.

But this also disables InputEvents to handle the KeyBown and KeyUp events from CoreWindow...

What should we do here to manage this behaviour following the guideline and yet leting the developer able to handle the "close" and/or "go to background" use cases?
